sequenceDiagram
    participant T as Tenant
    participant FE as Frontend
    participant STORAGE as Supabase Storage
    participant DB as Database
    participant M as Merchant
    participant V as Vendor

    Note over T,V: Tenant Creates Maintenance Request

    T->>FE: Navigate to /tenant/maintenance
    FE->>DB: Query tenant's active maintenance requests
    DB-->>FE: Return maintenance list
    
    T->>FE: Click "Create Maintenance Request"
    FE->>T: Show maintenance form
    
    T->>FE: Fill request details
    Note right of T: Required fields:<br/>- Title/Summary<br/>- Category<br/>- Description<br/>- Priority level<br/>- Preferred schedule
    
    T->>FE: Select category
    Note right of T: Categories:<br/>- Plumbing<br/>- Electrical<br/>- AC/Cooling<br/>- Furniture<br/>- Appliances<br/>- Cleaning<br/>- Pest Control<br/>- General
    
    T->>FE: Set priority level
    Note right of T: Priority:<br/>- Low (cosmetic issues)<br/>- Medium (inconvenience)<br/>- High (urgent but safe)<br/>- Critical (safety hazard)
    
    T->>FE: Upload issue photos (max 5)
    Note right of T: Photos help vendor understand:<br/>- Damage extent<br/>- Required materials<br/>- Urgency level
    
    loop For each photo
        FE->>FE: Validate image (max 5MB)
        FE->>STORAGE: Upload to maintenance-photos
        Note right of STORAGE: Path: maintenance/{request_id}/{timestamp}.jpg
        STORAGE-->>FE: Return photo URL
    end
    
    T->>FE: Add detailed description
    Note right of T: "AC in bedroom not cooling.<br/>Started 2 days ago.<br/>Prefer morning appointment."
    
    T->>FE: Submit maintenance request
    FE->>FE: Validate required fields
    
    FE->>DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_requests
    Note right of DB: tenant_id, property_id, unit_id,<br/>merchant_id (from tenant contract),<br/>category, priority, title,<br/>description, status: 'submitted',<br/>created_at
    
    DB-->>FE: Return request_id
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_photos (bulk)
    Note right of DB: request_id, photo_url,<br/>display_order
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_timeline
    Note right of DB: request_id, status: 'submitted',<br/>message: 'Request created by tenant',<br/>timestamp
    
    DB->>DB: Calculate SLA deadline
    Note right of DB: Based on priority:<br/>- Critical: 4 hours<br/>- High: 24 hours<br/>- Medium: 72 hours<br/>- Low: 7 days
    
    DB->>DB: UPDATE maintenance_requests SET
    Note right of DB: sla_deadline: calculated_time
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO notifications (merchant)
    Note right of DB: type: 'maintenance_request_new',<br/>request_id, tenant_name,<br/>priority, category
    
    DB->>DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
    
    DB-->>M: Email: "New Maintenance Request"
    Note right of M: Subject: [PRIORITY] AC Issue<br/>- Tenant: John Doe<br/>- Unit: Room 203<br/>- Category: AC/Cooling<br/>- View details button
    
    DB-->>M: Push notification: New maintenance request
    
    DB-->>T: Email: "Request Submitted"
    Note right of T: Request ID: #MR-2025-001<br/>Status: Under Review<br/>Track progress online
    
    FE->>T: Success: "Request submitted"
    FE->>T: Show ticket number + tracking link
    
    Note over M,V: Merchant Reviews & Assigns
    
    M->>FE: Navigate to /merchant/maintenance
    FE->>DB: Query maintenance requests
    Note right of DB: Filter options:<br/>- Status (pending/assigned/completed)<br/>- Priority<br/>- Property<br/>- Date range
    
    DB-->>FE: Return maintenance list
    
    FE->>M: Display maintenance dashboard
    Note right of M: Shows requests grouped by:<br/>- Pending assignment (red)<br/>- In progress (yellow)<br/>- Completed (green)<br/>With SLA countdown
    
    M->>FE: Click request to review
    FE->>DB: Query request details + photos + tenant info
    DB-->>FE: Return full request data
    
    FE->>M: Display request detail page
    Note right of M: Shows:<br/>- Tenant info<br/>- Issue description<br/>- Photos<br/>- Priority & SLA<br/>- Assign options
    
    M->>FE: Choose assignment method
    Note right of M: Options:<br/>1. Assign to internal technician<br/>2. Assign to vendor marketplace<br/>3. Handle personally
    
    alt Assign to Vendor Marketplace
        M->>FE: Click "Find Vendor"
        FE->>DB: Query suitable vendors
        Note right of DB: WHERE category matches request<br/>AND verified = true<br/>AND avg_rating >= 4.0<br/>ORDER BY distance, rating
        
        DB-->>FE: Return recommended vendors
        
        FE->>M: Display vendor list
        Note right of M: Each vendor shows:<br/>- Business name<br/>- Rating & reviews<br/>- Distance<br/>- Avg response time<br/>- Assign button
        
        M->>FE: Select vendor + click assign
        FE->>DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
        
        DB->>DB: UPDATE maintenance_requests SET
        Note right of DB: status: 'assigned_to_vendor',<br/>assigned_vendor_id,<br/>assigned_at: NOW(),<br/>assigned_by: merchant_id
        
        DB->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_timeline
        Note right of DB: status: 'assigned',<br/>message: 'Assigned to [Vendor Name]'
        
        DB->>DB: INSERT INTO notifications (vendor)
        Note right of DB: type: 'maintenance_job_assigned',<br/>request_id, property, issue
        
        DB->>DB: INSERT INTO notifications (tenant)
        Note right of DB: type: 'maintenance_assigned',<br/>vendor_name
        
        DB->>DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
        
        DB-->>V: Email: "New Maintenance Job"
        Note right of V: Job details:<br/>- Location: [Property]<br/>- Issue: AC not cooling<br/>- Priority: High<br/>- Accept/Reject buttons
        
        DB-->>V: Push: New maintenance job
        
        DB-->>T: Push: Vendor assigned
        DB-->>T: Email: "Technician Assigned"
        
        FE->>M: Success: "Vendor assigned"
        
    else Assign to Internal Technician
        M->>FE: Select internal technician
        FE->>DB: UPDATE maintenance_requests
        Note right of DB: assigned_technician_id (merchant staff)
        
        DB-->>M: Technician notified
        DB-->>T: Internal team assigned
    end
    
    Note over V,T: Vendor Accepts Job
    
    V->>FE: Navigate to /vendor/jobs
    FE->>DB: Query assigned maintenance jobs
    DB-->>FE: Return jobs WHERE assigned_vendor_id
    
    FE->>V: Display maintenance jobs
    Note right of V: Shows:<br/>- Pending acceptance<br/>- Active jobs<br/>- Completed jobs
    
    V->>FE: Click job to view details
    FE->>DB: Query job details + photos
    DB-->>FE: Return full job info
    
    FE->>V: Display job detail page
    Note right of V: Shows:<br/>- Issue description<br/>- Photos<br/>- Property address<br/>- Tenant contact<br/>- Accept/Reject buttons
    
    V->>FE: Click "Accept Job"
    FE->>DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
    
    DB->>DB: UPDATE maintenance_requests SET
    Note right of DB: status: 'accepted',<br/>accepted_at: NOW()
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_timeline
    Note right of DB: status: 'accepted',<br/>message: 'Vendor accepted the job'
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO notifications (tenant & merchant)
    Note right of DB: type: 'maintenance_accepted'
    
    DB->>DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
    
    DB-->>T: Push: Job accepted by vendor
    DB-->>M: Notification: Job accepted
    
    FE->>V: Show "Start Job" button
    
    Note over V,T: Job Execution & Updates
    
    V->>FE: Click "Start Job"
    FE->>DB: UPDATE maintenance_requests
    Note right of DB: status: 'in_progress',<br/>started_at: NOW()
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_timeline
    Note right of DB: status: 'in_progress',<br/>message: 'Vendor started working'
    
    DB-->>T: Push: Work in progress
    
    V->>FE: Add progress update
    Note right of V: "Checked AC unit.<br/>Needs new compressor.<br/>ETA: 2 hours"
    
    FE->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_updates
    Note right of DB: request_id, posted_by: vendor_id,<br/>message, timestamp
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO notifications (tenant & merchant)
    DB-->>T: Push: New update from vendor
    DB-->>M: Notification: Job update
    
    T->>FE: View maintenance detail page
    FE->>DB: Query request + timeline + updates
    DB-->>FE: Return complete history
    
    FE->>T: Display live timeline
    Note right of T: Timeline shows:<br/>- Request submitted<br/>- Assigned to vendor<br/>- Vendor accepted<br/>- Work started<br/>- Progress updates (real-time)
    
    T->>FE: Add reply/question
    Note right of T: "How much will parts cost?"
    
    FE->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_updates
    Note right of DB: posted_by: tenant_id
    
    DB-->>V: Push: New message from tenant
    
    Note over V,T: Job Completion
    
    V->>FE: Upload completion photos
    loop For each photo
        FE->>STORAGE: Upload completion proof
        STORAGE-->>FE: Return URL
    end
    
    V->>FE: Add completion notes
    Note right of V: "Replaced compressor.<br/>AC now working properly.<br/>Parts: Rp 300k, Labor: Rp 200k"
    
    V->>FE: Click "Mark as Completed"
    FE->>DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
    
    DB->>DB: UPDATE maintenance_requests SET
    Note right of DB: status: 'completed',<br/>completed_at: NOW(),<br/>completion_notes
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_photos (completion)
    Note right of DB: type: 'completion_proof'
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_timeline
    Note right of DB: status: 'completed',<br/>message: 'Job completed by vendor'
    
    DB->>DB: Calculate job payment
    Note right of DB: total_cost: 500000<br/>(parts + labor)
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO vendor_earnings
    Note right of DB: type: 'maintenance_job',<br/>request_id, amount: 500000,<br/>status: 'available'
    
    DB->>DB: UPDATE vendors.earnings_balance += 500000
    
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO notifications (tenant & merchant)
    Note right of DB: type: 'maintenance_completed'
    
    DB->>DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
    
    DB-->>T: Email: "Maintenance Completed"
    Note right of T: Job summary:<br/>- Issue resolved<br/>- Completion photos<br/>- Cost breakdown<br/>- Rate vendor button
    
    DB-->>T: Push: Please rate vendor service
    
    DB-->>M: Email: Job completed notification
    DB-->>V: Email: Payment credited
    
    FE->>V: Success: "Job completed, payment received"
    
    Note over T,M: Tenant Reviews Completion
    
    T->>FE: View completed maintenance
    FE->>DB: Query completed request
    DB-->>FE: Return completion details + photos
    
    FE->>T: Display completion summary
    Note right of T: Shows:<br/>- Completion photos<br/>- Vendor notes<br/>- Cost breakdown<br/>- Rate & review form
    
    T->>FE: Submit rating & review
    Note right of T: Rating: 5 stars<br/>Review: "Fast and professional.<br/>AC working perfectly now!"
    
    FE->>DB: INSERT INTO maintenance_reviews
    Note right of DB: request_id, vendor_id,<br/>rating, review_text
    
    DB->>DB: UPDATE vendors average rating
    Note right of DB: Recalculate avg_rating from all reviews
    
    DB-->>V: Notification: New review received
    
    FE->>T: Thank you message